ABUJA – First Lady, Aisha Buhari on Monday stormed the national Secretariat of the All Progressives Congress (APC) and demanded more support for women from the party’s leadership The First Lady who was accompanied by the wife of the Vice President, Dolapo Osinbajo and Paulin Tallen, the Women Affairs Minister held a lengthy meeting with the Chairman of the party Senator Abdullahi Adamu. Responding to reporters’ inquiries, Mrs Buhari said the team was at the Secretariat to congratulate the Abdullahi Adamu led APC leadership for the good work they are doing. -Advertisement- “We are here to congratulate the party chairman and to thank the whole party stewards for the work they doing and to also seek support for women, they should not be forgotten”, Aisha Buhari said. . The Women Affairs minister added . ” the first lady is here with her team to congratulate the national chairman for the opportunity God has given him to the party and to thank him for the good work he has started doing and finally not to forget women because women world is critically in all elective position.